      "creatureType": "",
      "blurb": "Pharmakos",
      "publicNotes": "<h3>Conversion notes (this module)</h3><p><strong>Role:</strong> the chamberlain whose treason opened Scarwall to Mandraivus. Caught, Kazavon broke both his ankles and left him to die; he crawled into the hills and lived weeks on worms. When he finally dragged himself back, <strong>the orcs had already slain Mandraivus</strong> — and amid the corpse-field gleamed Serithtial. The instant he grasped his 'reward,' he understood whom his betrayal had truly wronged: <strong>Zon-Kuthon himself</strong>. The god cursed him into a <strong>pharmakos</strong> — an 80-foot worm of scapegoated sin — and hurled him into the vault beneath the Star Tower to guard the blade forever (the gugs of H3 venerate him as a god-child of Rovagug). Now that the sword is needed to cleanse Kazavon from Ileosa, the Midnight Lord no longer cares; <em>the PCs are effectively his executioners</em>. His own vision haunts E10 (the @UUID[Compendium.cotct-pf2e-conversion.cotct-hazards.Actor.curseOfTheWorm01]{Curse of the Worm}), and only his death ends it.</p>",
      "privateNotes": ""
    },
