      "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/Passive.webp",
      "name": "Curse of Eternal Torment",
      "system": {
        "description": {
          "value": "<p>A pharmakos's abhorrent form is the result of a powerful curse, usually inflicted by a god. This curse grants immortality; a pharmakos does not need to eat, drink, or breath to survive, and cannot die of old age&mdash;nor can a pharmakos willingly end its own life. This curse also constantly racks the pharmakos with agony; the creature endures this torment to an extent that it is immune to all mental damage.</p>"
